{"title_page": "List of films featuring time loops", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis '''list of films featuring [[time loop]]s''' where characters experience the same period of time which is repeatedly resetting: when a certain condition is met, such as a death of a character or a clock reaches a certain time, the loop starts again, with one or more characters retaining the memories from the previous loop.<ref name=\"TTIPM\">{{cite|title=Time Travel in Popular Media|author1=Matthew Jones|author2=Joan Ormrod|year=2015|publisher=[[McFarland & Company]]|isbn=9780786478071}}</ref>{{rp|207}} The list provides the names and brief synopses of films in which time loops are a prominent plot device.\n\n==List==\n<!-- PLEASE ADD A FILM AND ITS CITATION IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Film \n! scope=\"col\" | Year \n! scope=\"col\" class=\"sortable\" style=white-space:nowrap | Description\n|-\n| ''[[12 Dates of Christmas]]'' || 2011 || Kate finds herself reliving [[Christmas Eve]] (including a blind date with a man named Miles) over and over again. She must discover how to break the cycle \u2013 should she attempt to win back her ex-boyfriend Jack, should she pursue Miles, or something else?<ref>{{cite web|last1=Griffiths|first1=John|title=12 Dates of Christmas|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/review--12-dates-of-christmas-2011612|website=[[US Weekly]]|accessdate=7 May 2014|date=6 December 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''12 Days of Christmas Eve'' || 2004 || Calvin is an executive and as Christmas nears he becomes so preoccupied in clinching a deal that he fails to notice the preparations being made for the holidays by his girlfriend and son. On Christmas Eve itself Calvin is hurt in an accident and it takes nurse Angie to make him realize how he can make up for lost time.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Geno|title=The Twelve Days of Christmas Eve|url=https://www.scaredstiffreviews.com/the-twelve-days-of-christmas-eve-2004-%E2%80%93-xmas-movie-review|website=[[Scared Stiff Reviews]]|accessdate=21 Jan 2019|date=2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[12:01 (1993 film)|12:01]]'' || 1993 || Office worker Barry Thomas is forced to relive the worst day of his life.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.tvguide.com/movie-news/Ask-FlickChick-Its-7932.aspx|title=It's like Groundhog Day, but different. What is it?|work=TV Guide|accessdate=2014-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328023603/http://movies.tvguide.com/movie-news/ask-flickchick-its-7932.aspx|archive-date=2014-03-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[12:01 PM (1990 film)|12:01 PM]]''  || 1990 || This is the first film adaptation of the short story \"[[12:01 PM]]\" by [[Richard A. Lupoff]], which was published in 1973 in ''[[The Magazine of Fantasy and Science Fiction]]''. It originally aired on [[cable television]] as part of the [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] ''30-Minute Movie'' anthology series. It was nominated for an [[Academy Award]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://awardsdatabase.oscars.org/ampas_awards/DisplayMain.jsp?curTime=1229994805425 |title=1990 (63rd): Short Film (Live Action) |work=Academy Awards Database |publisher=Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402164428/http://awardsdatabase.oscars.org/ampas_awards/DisplayMain.jsp?curTime=1229994805425 |archivedate=2015-04-02 }}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[About Time (2013 film)|About Time]]'' || 2013 || A 21-year-old man is given his family secret, the ability to travel back in time. His first goal is to find a girlfriend, and subsequent trials and errors lead him to appreciate ordinary happiness in life. <ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2194499/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[ARQ (film)|ARQ]]'' || 2016 || An engineer, whose invention causes time to loop during a home invasion, attempts to save his former lover, while learning who has targeted him and why.<ref>{{cite web|last1=T