ay|website=Radio Times|accessdate=6 May 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[A Day (film)|A Day]]'' || 2017 || A father attempts to save his daughter whilst stuck in an endless time loop.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Hyo-won|title=Cannes: South Korean Time Travel Film 'A Day' Sells to Multiple Territories|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-south-korean-film-a-day-sells-multiple-territories-1011010|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=25 September 2017|date=7 July 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Doctor Strange (2016 film)|Doctor Strange]]'' || 2016 || Stephen Strange traps himself and Dormmamu in a time loop in order to stop him from consuming the Earth.<ref>{{cite web |first=Aaron |last=Couch |title='Doctor Strange' Writer on Time-Bending Twist and What It Means for Marvel's Future |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/doctor-strange-end-screenwriter-explains-twist-944334 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=26 November 2016 |accessdate=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Edge of Tomorrow (film)|Edge of Tomorrow]]'' (also known as ''Live. Die. Repeat: Edge of Tomorrow) || 2014 || Maj. William \"Bill\" Cage ([[Tom Cruise]]) and Special Forces soldier Rita Vrataski ([[Emily Blunt]]) team up to fight a hostile alien race known as Mimics, with Cage continually returning to a repeating battle through a time loop.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-edge-of-tomorrow-trailer-tom-cruise-fights-an-eternal-battle-20140325,0,2975972.story|title='Edge of Tomorrow' trailer: Tom Cruise fights an eternal battle|author=Gettell, Oliver |date=2014-03-25|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2014-03-28}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Endless (film)|The Endless]]'' || 2017 || Two brothers return to a cult that is stuck in a time loop.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/04/lets-unpack-that-big-twist-in-the-endless.html|title=Unpacking That Big Twist in The Endless|last=Crucchiola|first=Jordan|work=[[Vulture.com]]|date=Apri